To obtain a regression estimate for unit-level population data, we first calculate the estimates b0, b1 and b2. This can be done with SAS/SURVEYREG procedure. Then using formula UE91hat = b0 + b1*HOU85 + b2*URB85 we calculate the fitted values to each population municipality. Finally we obtain the regression estimate for the total by summing all the fitted values over the population. This is possible in this case because the bias adjustment term in (3.32) is equal to zero.
